"Фильтрация/рассылка модулями OTRS/PostMaster (для более сложной "
"диспетчеризации)"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/email.xml:192
msgid ""
"If you use the bin/otrs.PostMaster.pl or bin/otrs.PostMasterMailbox.pl "
"method, you can insert or modify X-OTRS header entries with the PostMaster "
"filter modules. With the X-OTRS headers, the ticket system can execute some "
"actions on incoming mails, sort them into a specific queue, change the "
"priority or change the customer ID, for example. More information about the "
"X-OTRS headers are available in the section about <link linkend=\"adminarea-"
"postmasterpop3-account\">adding mail accounts</link> from the OTRS Admin "
"page."
msgstr ""
"Если вы используете метод bin/otrs.PostMaster.pl или bin/otrs."
"PostMasterMailbox.pl, то с модулем фильтрации PostMaster можно вставить или "
"модифицировать X-OTRS заголовок. С помощью X-OTRS-заголовков, система "
"обработки заявок может вызывать некоторые действия для входящих сообщений, "
"сортировать их в определенные очереди, или, например, изменять приоритет или "
"ID-клиента. Более подробную информацию о X-OTRS-заголовках можно найти в "
"главе <link linkend=\"adminarea-postmasterpop3-account\"> добавление "
"аккаунтов электронной почты </link> в Панели Администрирования."

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/email.xml:197
msgid "There are some default filter modules:"
msgstr "Есть некоторые предустановленные модули фильтрации:"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><note><para>
#: en/email.xml:202
msgid ""
"The job name (e.g. $Self-&gt;{'PostMaster::PreFilterModule'}-&gt;"
"{'JobName'}) needs to be unique!"
msgstr ""
"Название задания (например $Self-&gt;{'PostMaster::PreFilterModule'}-&gt;"
"{'JobName'}) должно быть уникальным!"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/email.xml:207
msgid ""
"Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::Match is a default module to match on "
"some email header (e.g. From, To, Subject, ...). It can set new email "
"headers (e.g. X-OTRS-Ignore: yes or X-OTRS-Queue: spam) if a filter rule "
"matches. The jobs of the Example 7-2 can be inserted in <filename>Kernel/"
"Config.pm</filename>"
msgstr ""
"Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::Match модуль по умолчанию для проверки "
"совпадения заголовков определенных емейлов (например \"От\", \"Кому\", \"Тема"
"\", ...). Он может устанавливать новые заголовки email (например X-OTRS-"
"Ignore: да или X-OTRS-Queue: spam) если совпадают правила совпадения. "
"Задания из Примера 7-2 могут быть прописаны в <filename>Kernel/Config.pm</"
"filename>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><example><title>
#: en/email.xml:211
msgid ""
"Example jobs for the filter module Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::Match"
msgstr ""
"Пример задания для модуля фильтрации Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::"
"Match"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><example><para><programlisting>
#: en/email.xml:215
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    # Job Name: 1-Match\n"
"    # (block/ignore all spam email with From: noreply@)\n"
"    $Self-&gt;{'PostMaster::PreFilterModule'}-&gt;{'1-Match'} = {\n"
"        Module =&gt; 'Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::Match',\n"
"        Match =&gt; {\n"
"            From =&gt; 'noreply@',\n"
"        },\n"
"        Set =&gt; {\n"
"            'X-OTRS-Ignore' =&gt; 'yes',\n"
"        },\n"
"    };\n"
"    # Job Name: 2-Match\n"
"    # (sort emails with From: sales@example.com and Subject: **ORDER**\n"
"    # into queue 'Order')\n"
"    $Self-&gt;{'PostMaster::PreFilterModule'}-&gt;{'2-Match'} = {\n"
"        Module =&gt; 'Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::Match',\n"
"        Match =&gt; {\n"
"            To =&gt; 'sales@example.com',\n"
"            Subject =&gt; '**ORDER**',\n"
"        },\n"
"        Set =&gt; {\n"
"            'X-OTRS-Queue' =&gt; 'Order',\n"
"        },\n"
"    };\n"
msgstr ""
"    # Job Name: 1-Match\n"
"    # (block/ignore all spam email with From: noreply@)\n"
"    $Self-&gt;{'PostMaster::PreFilterModule'}-&gt;{'1-Match'} = {\n"
"        Module =&gt; 'Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::Match',\n"
"        Match =&gt; {\n"
"            From =&gt; 'noreply@',\n"
"        },\n"
"        Set =&gt; {\n"
"            'X-OTRS-Ignore' =&gt; 'yes',\n"
"        },\n"
"    };\n"
"    # Job Name: 2-Match\n"
"    # (sort emails with From: sales@example.com and Subject: **ORDER**\n"
"    # into queue 'Order')\n"
"    $Self-&gt;{'PostMaster::PreFilterModule'}-&gt;{'2-Match'} = {\n"
"        Module =&gt; 'Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::Match',\n"
"        Match =&gt; {\n"
"            To =&gt; 'sales@example.com',\n"
"            Subject =&gt; '**ORDER**',\n"
"        },\n"
"        Set =&gt; {\n"
"            'X-OTRS-Queue' =&gt; 'Order',\n"
"        },\n"
"    };\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/email.xml:245
msgid ""
"Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::CMD is a default module to pipe the "
"email into an external command. The output is given to STDOUT and if the "
"result is true, then set new email header (e.g. X-OTRS-Ignore: yes or X-OTRS-"
"Queue: spam). The Example 7-3 can be used in <filename>Kernel/Config.pm</"
"filename>"
msgstr ""
"Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::CMD модуль по умолчанию для получения "
"емейлов для внешних команд. Вывод передается в STDOUT и если результат "
"истинна, то устанавливается новый заголовок (например X-OTRS-Ignore: да или "
"X-OTRS-Queue: spam). Пример 7-3 может быть использован в <filename>Kernel/"
"Config.pm</filename>"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><example><title>
#: en/email.xml:249
msgid ""
"Example job for the filter module Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::CMD"
msgstr ""
"Пример задания для модуля фильтрации Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::CMD"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><example><para><programlisting>
#: en/email.xml:253
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    # Job Name: 5-SpamAssassin\n"
"    # (SpamAssassin example setup, ignore spam emails)\n"
"    $Self-&gt;{'PostMaster::PreFilterModule'}-&gt;{'5-SpamAssassin'} = {\n"
"        Module =&gt; 'Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::CMD',\n"
"        CMD =&gt; '/usr/bin/spamassassin | grep -i \"X-Spam-Status: yes\"',\n"
"        Set =&gt; {\n"
"            'X-OTRS-Ignore' =&gt; 'yes',\n"
"        },\n"
"    };\n"
msgstr ""
"    # Job Name: 5-SpamAssassin\n"
"    # (SpamAssassin example setup, ignore spam emails)\n"
"    $Self-&gt;{'PostMaster::PreFilterModule'}-&gt;{'5-SpamAssassin'} = {\n"
"        Module =&gt; 'Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::CMD',\n"
"        CMD =&gt; '/usr/bin/spamassassin | grep -i \"X-Spam-Status: yes\"',\n"
"        Set =&gt; {\n"
"            'X-OTRS-Ignore' =&gt; 'yes',\n"
"        },\n"
"    };\n"

#. type: Content of: <chapter><section><section><para>
#: en/email.xml:268
msgid ""
"Of course it's also possible to develop your own PostMaster filter modules."
